RACE.RACE_TEXT: TURF PARADISE RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 9400. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $4,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMPASSIONED CLAIM sprinted clear soon after the start, saved ground while setting the pace, was well rated through the back-stretch and drew off through the lane with complete authority. WINTER SOLDIER lacked early speed, raced six-wide through the second turn and finished with good late energy to gain the place. ALEX'S DREAM raced unhurried early, saved ground through the second turn, angled out in mid-stretch and finished with a late bid. SUPER CREATIVE chased the leaders while racing three-wide and failed to gain in the drive. CLASS COMPOUNDS chased the leaders while racing four-wide, lugged out through the back-stretch and gradually gave way. DEPUTY KNIGHT was void of early speed, raced three-wide through the second turn and was not a factor. GABE'S MONSTER lacked early foot, raced five-wide through the second turn and did not offer a bid. SCRATCH ME chased the leaders from the inside for a half and weakened. THE RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

BURNIN VERNON showed no early speed, raced four-wide through the turn, angled in with a furlong to run and finished with good energy. NORTHERN COCKTAIL broke sharply to dispute the pace while racing three-wide from between foes and gave way after going a half.
